WORLD; 
BRITAIN, ARGENTINA TO OPEN TALKS 
Britain and Argentina agreed today to hold talks in Madrid in October on 
restoring diplomatic relations and renewing economic, cultural and sports ties 
ruptured since they went to war over the Falkland islands in 1982. 
Representatives of the two countries announced the breakthrough in London, 
Buenos Aires and the United Nations after several days of negotiations in New 
York. 
